main event: Two oblong, gold-colored objects were observed in the sky near Santa Maria, California on June 27, 1955.
interesting points: The objects were observed to be moving up and down.
The objects were described as being the size of a half dollar and were side by side.
The objects were initially reported as unidentified, but later concluded to be a balloon.
The report includes a description of the objects' appearance and movement, as well as the time and location of the sighting.
